1- to work with external database like MySQL u must provide the followings:
    1- Address          ->  127.0.0.1
    2- Port             -> 8000
    3- database name    -> django.dv.backends.mysql

2- Database Driver which is responsible for:
    mapping all the models and translating Python queries into SQL instructions via the model. 

3- to install mysql:
    brew install mysql

4- to access the database in the mysql terminal, run the following command:
    mysql -u root -p
    SHOW DATABASES;

3- to create a new database in the mysql terminal, run the following command:
    CREATE DATABASE django;

4- to create a new user in the mysql terminal, run the following command:
    CREATE USER 'django'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'password';

5- to grant all privileges to the new user:
    GRANT ALL ON *.* TO 'django'@'localhost';
    FLUSH PRIVILEGES;

6- to install the client mysqlclient - which must be installed at any new venv:
    pip install mysqlclient 
    allow django to connect to the database using the nessasry driver to communicate between them

7- to establish a connection to the database in the settings.py file, add the following:
    DATABASES = {
        'default': {
            'ENGINE': 'django.db.backends.mysql',
            'NAME': 'meta',
            'HOST': '127.0.0.1',
            'PORT': '3306',
            'USER': 'admindjango',
            'PASSWORD': 'password',
            'OPTIONS': {
                'read_default_file': 'etc/mysql/my.cnf',
            }
        },
    }

